article.headline: Houston 95, Grambling 52
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Andre Owens scored 26 points and Dwight Jones II added 15 as Houston beat Grambling State 95-52 Saturday night. Owens was 9-of-19 from the floor, including 4-of-9 on 3-pointers, and also recorded four steals for the Cougars (4-2). Lanny Smith added 13 points and Cedrick Hensley had 11 for UH. Grambling (2-1) was held to just 27 percent shooting. Marcus Watson led the Tigers with 20 points and seven rebounds, but he also had six of Grambling's 27 turnovers. The other four starters combined to shoot just 2-of-16. Houston jumped to a 38-20 halftime lead while giving up just six field goals. In the second half the Cougars went to the bench, as 11 players played at least 11 minutes.
